Sentencas: The evolution of performance degradation has become a major obstacle to the long-life operation of the Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) system.
Titulo: Real-Time State of Health Estimation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Unscented Kalman Filter

Sentencas: The feasibility of employing degradation resistance to assess the State of Health (SOH) is proposed and verified.
Titulo: Real-Time State of Health Estimation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Unscented Kalman Filter

Sentencas: In addition, a real-time Unscented Kalman Filter (UKF) based SOH estimation method is further proposed to eliminate the disturbance of calculating the SOH directly utilizing measurement and electric balance model.
Titulo: Real-Time State of Health Estimation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Unscented Kalman Filter

Sentencas: The results of real-time SOH estimation with an UKF under constant and varying load conditions demonstrate the feasibility and effectiveness of the SOFC performance degradation assessment method.
Titulo: Real-Time State of Health Estimation for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Based on Unscented Kalman Filter
